# command 

hadoop fs -rm -r -skipTrash /path/to/parent/directory/*/

explaination - this will do the needfully cleanup of empty directories
-rm = remove the directory
-r = does recursively delete


hadoop fs -find /path/to/parent/directory -type d -empty -delete

explaination - 
find = used to find a file/dir
-type = for specifying type
d - for serching directory
-empty = condition according to question
-delete = simply delete the directory


